    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100K77/79.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Dominican Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg your acceptance of my appreciative thanks
                    for your thoughtful courtesy in communicating to me, which you did by your note
                    of the 4th instant, the text of the cablegram which you received from your
                    Government concerning the visit of the Secretary of State to the Dominican
                    Republic.</p>
                <p>I can not but express to you my satisfaction at the cordial welcome which it
                    conveys, so in harmony with the friendship which has consistently moved the
                    Dominican Government in its relations with the United States.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
